  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 220°C/ 200°C (fan)/ gas 7</p><p>Cut your <strong>potatoes</strong> (skins on) into thin fries</p><p>Add the <strong>fries </strong>to a baking tray (or two!) with a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong> and a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and <strong>pepper</strong></p><p>Give everything a good mix up and put the tray[s] in the oven for an initial 20-25 min or until golden and crisp</p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1583251211787-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1583251211787-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1583251211787-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1583251211787-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1583251211787-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>While the fries are cooking, add your<strong> beef mince</strong> to a bowl with your<strong> panko breadcrumbs</strong> and a generous pinch of<strong> salt </strong>and<strong> pepper</strong></p><p>Give everything a good mix up until fully combined (clean hands is the best way!) then equally divide and shape into 1 patty per person</p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1583251069648-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1583251069648-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1583251069648-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1583251069648-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1583251069648-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add the<strong> burger patty[ies]</strong> to an oiled baking tray with your<strong> streaky bacon</strong></p><p>Tip: Cooking for 3 or more? Use 2 trays!</p><p>Put the tray[s] in the oven for 15-20 min or until the burger[s] is browned and cooked through (no pink meat!) and the bacon is crispy</p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1583251073555-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1583251073555-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1583251073555-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1583251073555-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1583251073555-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, peel and finely chop (or grate) your <strong>garlic</strong></p><p>Chop your <strong>parsley</strong> roughly, including the stalks</p><p>Chop a large knob of <strong>butter </strong>into small cubes</p><p>Peel your<strong> Italian hard cheese</strong> with a peeler until you end up with a pile of cheese shavings</p>",
      "order": 4,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-1583251077190-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-1583251077190-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-1583251077190-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-1583251077190-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-1583251077190-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once the fries are golden, remove them from the oven and push to one side of the tray[s], then top the fries with the <strong>cubed butter</strong>,<strong> garlic </strong>and <strong>parsley </strong>and gently toss everything together – these are your <strong>garlic butter fries</strong></p><p>Slice your <strong>brioche bun[s]</strong> in half and add to the tray[s] (cut side up!)</p><p>Return the tray[s] to the oven for 4-5 min or until the butter has melted and the brioche is warmed through</p>",
      "order": 5,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-5-1583251081880-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-5-1583251081880-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-5-1583251081880-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-5-1583251081880-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-5-1583251081880-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once the burger[s] is cooked through, remove the tray[s]<span class=\"text-danger\"> </span>from the oven and top each patty with the <strong>Italian hard cheese shavings</strong></p><p>Return to the oven for 2-3 min or until the cheese has melted – this is your <strong>cheesy beef patty</strong></p><p>Tip: If your bacon is already crispy at this point, add it to a plate and set aside</p>",
      "order": 6,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-6-1583251085401-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-6-1583251085401-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-6-1583251085401-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-6-1583251085401-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-6-1583251085401-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Roughly chop your <strong>tomato[es]</strong></p><p>Wash your <strong>salad</strong>, then pat dry with kitchen paper</p><p>Reserve a<span class=\"text-danger\"> </span>handful of <strong>salad</strong> for your burger, then toss the <strong>remaining salad</strong> and the <strong>chopped tomato </strong>with a drizzle of<span class=\"text-danger\"> </span><strong>olive oil</strong> and your <strong>balsamic vinegar </strong>– this is your <strong>dressed salad</strong></p><p>Add your <strong>truffle oil</strong> to a small bowl along with your <strong>mayo</strong> and a generous grind of <strong>black pepper </strong>and mix it all together – this is your <strong>truffle mayo</strong></p>",
      "order": 7,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-7-1583251089348-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-7-1583251089348-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-7-1583251089348-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-7-1583251089348-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-7-1583251089348-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>To build your burger, spread the <strong>warmed</strong> <strong>brioche base</strong> with a dollop of <strong>onion marmalade</strong>, then add the <strong>cheesy beef patty</strong> followed by the <strong>crispy bacon</strong>, a spoonful of<strong> truffle mayo</strong>, the <strong>reserved</strong> <strong>salad </strong>and top with a <strong>warmed brioche lid</strong> – this is your<strong> bacon cheeseburger</strong></p><p>Serve the <strong>dressed salad </strong>and <strong>garlic butter fries</strong> to the side with any <strong>remaining</strong> <strong>truffle</strong> <strong>mayo</strong></p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
      "order": 8,
